RED OAK POWER, LLC REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Red Oak Power, LLC (“Red Oak”) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service (“Reactive Service”) from an electric generation facility located in Sayreville, New Jersey (“Facility”) that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Red Oak’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
Total charges for any twelve-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $1,800,000.00. The total monthly revenue requirement is $1,800,000.00 / 12 = $150,000.00.
